						               													<description>Bloody Broadsides &amp;ndash; is a fast paced Napoleonic Naval game which allows you to Captain one or more massive ships of the line from the Age of Sail.  Most games can be played in 3 hours.  This game is intended to play with miniature ships on a large hex mat.  These rules were written specifically for Portsmouth Miniatures and Games 1:900 scale ships but may be used with any miniatures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games may be as small as one on one Captain Duels, up to massive 60 ships or more historical battles like the Battle of Trafalgar.  There is a point system to allow you to design your own scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Features:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Plotted Movement&amp;#10;Simultaneous Combat&amp;#10;Point System&amp;#10;Crew Grade&amp;#10;Morale Checks&amp;#10;Ship Classes (1st rate through 4th rate)&amp;#10;Critical Hits (including Ship Explodes)&amp;#10;Raking&amp;#10;Grappling&amp;#10;Capturing Ships&amp;#10;Drifting&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
